.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-TOPOLOGY 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.8.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-topology \- Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard topology [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.PP
Use this when you need a graph view of dashboards, folders, variables, datasource links, and optional alert contract data. The command also accepts the graph alias.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-governance
dashboard governance JSON input.
.TP
.B \-\-queries
optional dashboard query\-report JSON input.
.TP
.B \-\-alert\-contract
optional alert contract JSON input.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format
render text, json, mermaid, or dot.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-file
write the rendered topology to disk.
.TP
.B \-\-interactive
open the interactive terminal browser.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard topology \
.EE
.PP
Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.EX
  --governance ./governance.json \
.EE
.PP
Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.EX
  --queries ./queries.json \
.EE
.PP
Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.EX
  --alert-contract ./alert-contract.json \
.EE
.PP
Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.EX
  --output-format mermaid
.EE
